title: A1466 820-00165-A no boot
message:
Hi,

I have an A1466 820-00165-A that has no power.
I have green light but no fan spin and no usb activity.

On PP5V_S5 i only have 1.1V, and U7501 pins 14 and 29, also have 1.1V on PP5V_S5.
U7501 EN has 3.4V

Can you help?

title: A1466 820-00165-A no boot
message: Post more pins voltage for U7501; 23, 22, 12, 13, 29, 21.

title: A1466 820-00165-A no boot
message:
You don't have PPBUS_G3H and complain the board doesn't turn on???
Find why is not present.
Start checking in diode mode.

title: A1466 820-00165-A no boot
message:
Hi,
But I have  PPBUS_G3H  8.57V. Don't understand

title: A1466 820-00165-A no boot
message:
Hi,
you're right. I have a blown cap C7583, and the trace of it has gone. I've made a jumper from Q7560 to C7581, but still doesn't work, and I can't find any other broken trace. U7501 still has 0.9V on pin 23.
Q7560 has 8.57V on PPBUS_S5_HS_OTHER_ISNS

title: A1466 820-00165-A no boot
message:
OK, .  you're right I've made a jumper from Q7560 to C7500, and now it works.
It seams a broken trace inside the board. Is there any better way to "wire" those, besides passing a cable all the board extension to the other side?

title: A1466 820-00165-A no boot
message: Search on the same side other power rails derivated from PPBUS_G3H.
